                        <p>Fort Collins is located in the foothills of the Rocky Mountains, about an hour drive from Denver—Colorado's largest city. The population of Fort Collins is about 155,000, perfect for a mid-size town. With more than 300 days of sunshine a year, 90 parks and natural areas and 450 kilometers of trails, it's also less than an hour drive to two major ski resorts.</p>
<p>There are also more than 600 restaurants in the Fort Collins area and more than 300 local events each year. Watch a concert in Old Town or enjoy a cultural event at the city’s International Center. While exploring the city’s many cycling and walking trails or swimming in Horsetooth Reservoir, you will appreciate the beauty of our natural surroundings. For more exciting tips about living in Fort Collins, visit our <a href="https://www.intostudy.com/downloads/city-guides/us/CSU_City_Guide_2019-20v2_Hyperlinks.pdf">City Guide</a>.</p>

